results.name: a(n) = 1, a(n+1) = smallest number not occurring earlier, having with a(n) neither a common digit nor a common divisor.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: f v ws = g ws where
g (x:xs) = if gcd v x == 1 && ((intersect `on` show) v x == "")
then x : f x (delete x ws) else g xs

(PARI) {u=[]; a=1; for(n=1,99, print1(a","); u=setunion(u,[a]); while(#u>1&&u[2]==u[1]+1,u=u[^1]); for(k=u[1]+1,9e9, setsearch(u,k)&&next;gcd(k,a)>1&&next; #setintersect(Set(digits(a)),Set(digits(k)))&&next; a=k; next(2)));a} \\ _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 17 2016
